Defendant Ehtoo La in court with Attorney Robert J. Dvorak.  
Erin M. Karshen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

**CASE HEARD BY BRANCH 44 FOR BRANCH 15**

Matter before the Court for Sentencing.  Hearing proceeded.   Sworn: Karen Interpreter Wilfred Tunbaw.  Statements made by the state, defense and defendant.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 

-Defendant is informed he may not possess and/or own any firearms

-Defendant ordered  to provide DNA sample

-Defendant is informed he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been reinstated

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 42 MONTHS with credit for 1 day. 

The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS.  

The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 24 MONTHS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Serve 90 days in the House of Correction with release privileges for employment, counseling and treatment with NO good time allowed- STAYED for agent use;
*Obtain AODA assessment and complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Cooperate with sex offender evaluation and cooperate with recommended treatment and counseling;
*No involvement in conduct rising to the level of finding of probable cause;
*No contact with victim as follows:  during term of probation: ONLY if victim agrees and notifies the agent and agent agrees/ IF REVOKED NO CONTACT;
*Seek/maintain employment;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges (including dna), fees, assessments, and costs by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment (collection under Wisc. Stat. 71.935);

The Court allows the defendant to travel to Chicago, IL and/or Minneapolis/St. Paul, MN for the purpose of counseling and treatment.  The Court ordered restitution set at zero.  Request to waive sex offender reporting made by defense; state takes no position.  The Court sets forth findings under sec. 301.45; defense request to waive reporting granted by the Court.  The Court advised the defendant of his right to appeal this sentence. 
Filed;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
-Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgment;
-Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence-copy to defendant;
-Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
